title._content: Grupp jaapanlasi / A group of Japanese

description._content: „Nadežda“ Jaapanis viibimise ajal 1804-1805 aastal oli keisririik välismaalaste jaoks veel suuresti suletud. Ainsana eurooplastest oli Nagasaki linna kaudu kontakt Jaapaniga lubatud hollandlastele, sinna suundusid venelased. - - - During Nadezhda’s stay in Japan between 1804-1805, the empire was still closed off for foreigners. The Dutch were the only Europeans who were allowed contact with Japan through the city of Nagasaki, where the Russians also headed.
